World War II Munitions Discovered in Central China
CHANGSHA , November 19 ( Xinhua ) -- More than 100 World War II artillery shells were recently found in the Changsha Section of the Xiangjiang River in central China 's Hunan Province .
The shells , including mortar shells , high velocity bullets , hand grenades and antitank explosives , were discover in the dry river bed .
Explosive experts said eroded casings made the explosive highly dangerous .
The shells have been recovered and transferred to a safe site .
Experts warned local residents to avoid the area which might contain additional explosives .
The water level has dropped dramatically since early October due to the serious drought in the upper reaches of the river , and damming project in the upstream Hengyang Section .
